snippet: Five geckos launched into space for an experiment on sexual reproduction in near-zero gravity were found dead after their spacecraft returned to earth, the Russian space agency said.
abstract: Five geckos launched into space by Russia for experiment on sexual reproduction in near-zero gravity are found dead after spacecraft returns to earth.
lead_paragraph: Five geckos launched into space for an experiment on sexual reproduction in near-zero gravity were found dead after their spacecraft returned to earth, the Russian space agency said.

headline.main: Geckos on Mission Die Aboard Russian Spacecraft
headline.print_headline: Russia: Geckos on a Mission Perish on Their Spacecraft
